        <link rel="icon" href="/public/assets/favicon.webp" type="image/x-icon">
        <!-- Page Title -->
        <title>Security Control Simulation System</title>

    </head>
<body>
    <!-- Navigation Bar -->
    <nav class="custom-navbar">
        <div class="navbar-logo">
            <a>SCSS</a>
        </div>

    </nav>

    <section class="info" id="no-advisor" div class="text-center" style="display: none; ">
        <h1><b>TASK DESCRIPTION</b></h1>
        <p>You are a cyber defence expert working within the Emergency Services Cyberdefense Division, your role is to review incoming data packets and protect the network by classifying them as "Trusted", "Suspect", or "Hostile" based on the information provided. Incorrect or missed classifications may lead to Cyberdefence breaches which would have an impact on the ability of the Emergency Services to function.</p>
        <div class="text-center" style="margin-top: 20px;">
            <img src="../public/assets/Explanation1.png" alt="Labelled Cyber Defence System" class="img-fluid" style="max-width: 400px; height: auto;">
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center;">
            <button onclick="proceed()">Continue</button>
          </div>
    </section>
    <section class="info" id="ai-advisor" style="display: none;">
        <h1><b>TASK DESCRIPTION</b></h1>
        <p>You are a cyber defence expert working within the Emergency Services Cyberdefense Division, your role is to review incoming data packets and protect the network by classifying them as "Trusted", "Suspect", or "Hostile" based on the information provided. Incorrect or missed classifications may lead to Cyberdefence breaches which would have an impact on the ability of the Emergency Services to function.</p>
        <P>You have been provided with access to reccomendations from an A.I who was given the same information as yourself, which will be shown below</P>
        <div class="text-center" style="margin-top: 20px;">
            <img src="../public/assets/Explanation1.png" alt="Labelled Cyber Defence System" class="img-fluid" style="max-width: 400px; height: auto;">
        </div>
        
        <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center;">
            <button onclick="proceed()">Continue</button>
          </div>
    </section>
    <section class="info" id="human-advisor" style="display: none;">
        <h1><b>TASK DESCRIPTION</b></h1>
        <p>You are a cyber defence expert working within the Emergency Services Cyberdefense Division, your role is to review incoming data packets and protect the network by classifying them as "Trusted", "Suspect", or "Hostile" based on the information provided. Incorrect or missed classifications may lead to Cyberdefence breaches which would have an impact on the ability of the Emergency Services to function.</p>
        <p>You have been provided with access to reccomendations from a previous participent who was given the same information as yourself, which will be shown below</p>
        <div class="text-center" style="margin-top: 20px;">
            <img src="../public/assets/Explanation1.png" alt="Labelled Cyber Defence System" class="img-fluid" style="max-width: 400px; height: auto;">
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center;">
            <button onclick="proceed()">Continue</button>
          </div>
    </section>
    <script>
        var condition = "<%= condition %>";

        switch (condition) {
            case "noAdvisor":
                document.getElementById("no-advisor").style.display = "block";
                break;
            case "aiAdvisor":
                document.getElementById("ai-advisor").style.display = "block";
                break;
            case "humanAdvisor":
                document.getElementById("human-advisor").style.display = "block";
                break;
        }

        function proceed() {
            window.location.href = "/information/rules"
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>